<subSubSection id="909454EAFFFCA428FF75FB2DFEC96FE5" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D8310761FFFCA428FF75FB2DFEC96FE5" blockId="54.[151,1437,151,1905]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FF75FB2DFE886FC9" bold="true" box="[199,335,1195,1221]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FD8EFB2DFD766FC9" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[572,689,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FD8EFB2DFD766FC9" box="[572,689,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is derived from Ross &amp; Michelbacher collecting the 
<typeStatus id="0735B9C3FFFCA428FAB2FB2DFA906FC9" box="[1280,1367,1195,1221]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">syntype</typeStatus>
series in 
<collectingCountry id="A09947F1FFFCA428FF06FB49FECD6FE5" box="[180,266,1231,1257]" name="Bolivia" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="909454EAFFFCA428FF75FB74FDC46DB1" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D8310761FFFCA428FF75FB74FDC46DB1" blockId="54.[151,1437,151,1905]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FF75FB74FE8B6E00" bold="true" box="[199,332,1266,1292]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FEE7FB75FD446E01" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[341,643,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FEE7FB75FD446E01" box="[341,643,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pogonomyrmex bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not known to co-occur with any congeners, but note that very few series of 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FF4FFA91FE6A6E3C" box="[253,429,1303,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FF4FFA91FE6A6E3C" box="[253,429,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pogonomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been collected from the Bolivian altiplano. Regardless, 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FBD6FA91FB3F6E3D" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[1124,1272,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FBD6FA91FBB26E3C" box="[1124,1141,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FB31FA91FB3F6E3D" box="[1155,1272,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily diagnosed by longitudinal striae that cover only the anterior one-third to one-half of the first gastral tergum with the rest of the tergum smooth and polished, strongly shining. 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FD57FAD9FC3D6E74" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[741,1018,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atacama">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FD57FAD9FC3D6E74" box="[741,1018,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pogonomyrmex atacama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species with this character that is likely to be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FDBFFA05FD5A6E91" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[525,669,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FDBFFA05FD5A6E91" box="[525,669,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FD78FA05FC9D6E91" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[714,858,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FD78FA05FC9D6E91" box="[714,858,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (1) the posterior corners of head rugose, (2) longitudinal rugae on dorsum of promesonotum irregular, continuing to anterior margin of pronotum, (3) mandibles with six teeth, (4) rugae on dorsum of postpetiole mostly transverse, and (5) rugae on frontal triangle subparallel-parallel, continuing onto clypeus. In 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FE6AFA69FD926D04" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[472,597,1519,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atacama">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FE6AFA69FD926D04" box="[472,597,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. atacama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (1) the posterior corners of head smooth and shining to strongly shining for most to all workers in a series, (2) mandibles with seven teeth, (3) longitudinal rugae on dorsum of mesonotum regular; anterior margin of pronotum usually with one to few transverse rugae, (4) rugae on dorsum of postpetiole mostly longitudinal, and (5) one to few rugae on frontal triangle converging anterad forming a narrowly rounded V-shaped pattern. 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FED3F9F9FD466D94" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[353,641,1663,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cusquena">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FED3F9F9FD466D94" box="[353,641,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pogonomyrmex cusquena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is another congener from high elevation habitats, but 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FB67F9F9FA9A6D94" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[1237,1373,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cusquena">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FB67F9F9FB216D94" box="[1237,1254,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FB41F9F9FA9A6D94" box="[1267,1373,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">cusquena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks striae on the first gastral tergum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="909454EAFFFCA428FF75F940FC2C6C7D" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="D8310761FFFCA428FF75F940FC2C6C7D" blockId="54.[151,1437,151,1905]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FF75F940FEE06DEC" bold="true" box="[199,295,1734,1760]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Biology.</emphasis>
Nothing is known about the biology of 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FD5BF941FCBD6DED" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[745,890,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FD5BF941FCBD6DED" box="[745,890,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The collection locale for the 
<typeStatus id="0735B9C3FFFCA428FB79F941FAE56DED" box="[1227,1314,1735,1761]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">syntype</typeStatus>
series was given only as 
<quantity id="1F76AA84FFFCA428FE84F96CFEB06C09" box="[310,375,1770,1797]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.242048" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="mi" value="45.0">45 mi</quantity>
south of 
<collectingRegion id="1A4AC983FFFCA428FE50F96DFDF56C09" box="[482,562,1771,1797]" country="Bolivia" name="La Paz" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">La Paz</collectingRegion>
, which is within the Bolivian altiplano at an elevation that likely ranges from 
<quantity id="1F76AA84FFFCA428FF25F889FEF06C25" box="[151,311,1807,1833]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.09" metricValueMax="4.24" metricValueMin="3.94" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="4090.0" valueMax="4240.0" valueMin="3940.0">3940â€“4240 m</quantity>
. It seems likely that 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FD94F889FD7E6C25" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[550,697,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FD94F889FD7E6C25" box="[550,697,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to altiplano habitats of 
<collectingCountry id="A09947F1FFFCA428FBE5F889FB6E6C25" box="[1111,1193,1807,1833]" name="Bolivia" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and probably nearby areas of 
<collectingCountry id="A09947F1FFFCA428FF4AF8B5FEE86C41" box="[248,303,1843,1869]" name="Peru" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Peru</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="1F8E7CE2FFFCA428FE88F8B5FDA06C41" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[314,615,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pogonomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FE88F8B5FDA06C41" box="[314,615,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pogonomyrmex bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the type locality, which appears to be in the Central Andean dry puna ecoregion, as defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="BC1F7A90FFFCA428FDCAF8D1FC8C6C7D" author="Olson, D. M. &amp; Dinerstein, E. &amp; Wikramanayake, E. D. &amp; Burgess, N. D. &amp; Powell, G. V. N. &amp; Underwood, E. C. &amp; D'Amico, J. A. &amp; Itoua, I. &amp; Strand, H. E. &amp; Morrison, J. C. &amp; Loucks, C. J. &amp; Allnutt, T. F. &amp; Ricketts, T. H. &amp; Kura, Y. &amp; Lamoreux, J. F. &amp; Wettengel, W. W. &amp; Hedao, P. &amp; Kassem, K. R." box="[632,843,1879,1905]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="933 - 938" refId="ref148173" refString="Olson, D. M., Dinerstein, E., Wikramanayake, E. D., Burgess, N. D., Powell, G. V. N., Underwood, E. C., D'Amico, J. A., Itoua, I., Strand, H. E., Morrison, J. C., Loucks, C. J., Allnutt, T. F., Ricketts, T. H., Kura, Y., Lamoreux, J. F., Wettengel, W. W., Hedao, P. &amp; Kassem, K. R. (2001) Terrestrial ecoregions of the world: a new map of life on Earth. Bioscience, 51 (11), 933 - 938. https: // doi. org / 10.1641 / 0006 - 3568 (2001) 051 [0933: TEOTWA] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Olson 
<emphasis id="EAFADB73FFFCA428FD70F8D1FD346C7D" box="[706,755,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al</emphasis>
. (2001)
</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation id="40B51BE4FFFCA428FCE8F8D1FC196C7D" box="[858,990,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[423,1160,181,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-15@51.[423,1165,181,1891]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 22. Geographic distribution of: (A) Pogonomyrmex atratus, (B) P. bolivianus, and (C) P. carbonarius. The large black circle in each panel denotes the type locality. See text regarding the type locality for P. atratus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5499186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5499186/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figure 22B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
